{{Motorsport season |series = European Rallycross Championship |year = 1985 |previous = 1984 | next = 1986 }}
[[File:MikaelNordström4WDBeetle1985.jpg|thumb|[[Mikael Nördstrom]] at the Finnish round of the championship]] The '''1985 European Rallycross Championship season''' was the tenth season of the [[FIA European Rallycross Championship]] under that name and the thirteenth season overall since it began as the [[Embassy/ERA European Rallycross Championship]]. It was held across nine rounds starting at the [[Thermoton-Ring]] in [[Austria]] on March 31 and ending at the [[Eurocircuit]] in the [[Netherlands]] on October 13.
The champions were [[Anders Norstedt]] (Division 1) who defended his title and [[Matti Alamäki]] (Division 2).
