{{Infobox song contest country |Name = Andorra |Member station = [[Ràdio i Televisió d'Andorra|RTVA]] |National selection event = {{Collapsible list | title = '''National Final''' | 2004–2005 | 2009 }}{{Collapsible list | title = '''Internal Selection''' | 2006–2008 }} |ESC apps = 6 (0 finals) |ESC first = [[Eurovision Song Contest 2004|2004]] |ESC last = [[Eurovision Song Contest 2009|2009]] |ESC best = 12th <small>SF</small>: [[Eurovision Song Contest 2007|2007]] |ESC worst = Last: [[Eurovision Song Contest 2006|2006 <small>SF</small>]] {{ref|a|1}} |Website = |EBU page = https://eurovision.tv/country/andorra |Current = 2009 }} '''[[Andorra]]''' has participated in the '''Eurovision Song Contest''' six times, debuting in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2004|2004 contest]]. Interest in the contest had been great for a long time, despite the local Andorran broadcaster, [[Ràdio i Televisió d'Andorra|Ràdio i Televisió d'Andorra (RTVA)]], not showing the contest until recent years (citizens could watch it on [[Spain|Spanish]] and [[France|French]] stations). A majority of the songs have so far been sung in [[Catalan language|Catalan]], the [[national language]] of Andorra.
As of 2019, Andorra is the only country to have participated in the contest and never to have featured in the final.
==Participation== Despite the homeland interest in the competition, Andorra has never qualified for the final. In 2007, a qualification for the final was predicted, but with a 12th-place finish, it just missed out. In the past RTVA held a large [[reality show]] contest to select its entry for Eurovision. From [[Eurovision Song Contest 2006|2006]], RTVA held an internal selection process to select the Andorran entry for the Eurovision Song Contest.
RTVA confirmed its participation in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2009|2009 contest]] in [[Moscow]], [[Russia]]. It announced that there would be a public selection process - something not seen in the country since 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://esctoday.com/12271/andorra_will_participate_at_eurovision_2009|title=Andorra will participate at Eurovision 2009|last=Hondal|first=Víctor|date=11 September 2008|publisher=ESCToday|website=esctoday.com|accessdate=11 September 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.esctoday.com/12415/andorra_prepares_for_eurovision_2009|title=Andorra prepares for Eurovision 2009!|last=Jiandani|first=Sanjay|date=22 October 2008|publisher=ESCToday|website=esctoday.com|accessdate=22 October 2008}}</ref> Andorra's 2009 entry once again failed to qualify, getting only 8 points in the semifinal.
In the finals, Andorra has always given its 12 points to Spain, with the exception of 2007. As the two nations are neighbouring, this has done very little to dispel accusations of political voting which have been going on for a long time. In December 2009, RTVA announced that Andorra would withdraw from the 2010 Contest due to a lack of funding for an Andorran entry. This came after RTVA submitted an entry for the contest, in case funding could be found to submit an entry. However no funding could be found, and so Andorra was forced to withdraw.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://esctoday.com/14492/upd-_andorra_submit_application_to_ebu|title=Andorra submit application to EBU|last=Hondal|first=Victor|date=13 November 2009|publisher=ESCToday|website=esctoday.com|accessdate=13 November 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://esctoday.com/14611/definitely_no_andorra_in_oslo|title=Definitely, no Andorra in Oslo|last=Victor|first=Hondal|date=12 December 2009|publisher=ESCToday|website=esctoday.com|accessdate=12 December 2009}}</ref>
Andorra did not participate in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2011|2011 contest]] due to financial difficulties,<ref>{{cite web|last=Jiandani|first=Sanjay|url=http://esctoday.com/16164/confirmed_andorra_will_not_return_in_2011|title=Confirmed: Andorra will not return in 2011|publisher=ESCToday|website=esctoday.com|accessdate=6 October 2010|date=6 October 2010}}</ref> or in the 2012 contest, for the same reason. Andorra did not participate in subsequent contests.
== EBU withdrawal == On 8 November 2011, it was announced by the Andorran broadcaster, RTVA, that they would leave the EBU, due to financial reasons and a cut of subsidies from the Andorran government.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.escdaily.com/andorra-rtva-to-quit-the-european-broadcasting-union/|title=Andorra: RTVA to quit the European Broadcasting Union|last=Van Ee|first=Dennis|website=escdaily.com|publisher=ESCDaily|accessdate=10 November 2011|date=10 November 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130616040548/http://www.escdaily.com/andorra-rtva-to-quit-the-european-broadcasting-union/|archive-date=2013-06-16|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> After a meeting with the EBU director Ingrid Deltenre in June 2012, RTVA decided to stay in the EBU, but said participation in Eurovision is still unlikely.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hondal|first=Victor|url=http://esctoday.com/36855/andorra-to-stay-in-ebu-no-eurovision-return-expected|title=Andorra to stay in EBU, no Eurovision return planned|website=esctoday.com|publisher=ESCToday|accessdate=20 June 2012|date=20 June 2012}}</ref>
