{{Orphan|date=May 2015}}

'''Bac u kry''' is a [[Slogan]] which was used during [[Kosovo|Kosovo's]]{{ref label|status|a|}} independence from [[Serbia]] in February 2008. It means ''Uncle, It is done!''<ref name="unclueitsdone">{{cite news |title=Joy and defiance on Kosovo's greatest day|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2008/feb/17/serbia.kosovo|publisher=The Guardian|date=February 17, 2008|accessdate=March 9, 2010 | location=London | first=Peter | last=Beaumont}}</ref>

The slogan was also used on T-shirts, pens and posters. The creators of this phrase say that this symbolizes the independence which many [[Ethnic Albanian]]s dreamt for since the end of the [[Kosovo War]] in 1999.<ref name="unclueitsdone"/>

The slogan often accompanies the face of [[Adem Jashari]], an Ethnic Albanian [[Commander]] during the [[Kosovo War]] who was killed in action.<ref name="unclueitsdone"/>

==Uses==
The slogan '''Bac u kry''' was used by many. There are [[billboard (advertising)|billboard]]s which use this phrase. In addition, in downtown Borroramizi ([[Pallati i Rinisë]]) there is a flag with exactly the same expression.

