The '''Catholic Church in Ghana''' is part of the worldwide [[Catholic Church]], under the spiritual leadership of the [[pope]] in [[Rome]].<ref name="Catholic Church in Ghana"/>
There are three million Catholics in [[Ghana]] and the country is divided into 20 [[diocese]]s including four [[archdiocese]]s and 1 Vicariate.<ref name="Catholic Church in Ghana">{{cite news|url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/country/gh.html|title=Catholic Church in Ghana |work= |publisher =catholic-hierarchy.org|date=|accessdate = 25 April 2012}}</ref>
[[Image:Cardinal Tukson 987.jpg|right|thumb|250px|[[Peter Turkson]] is the Ghanaian [[Cardinal (Catholicism)|Cardinal]] of the [[Catholic Church]]]]
*[[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Accra|Accra]] **[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Ho|Ho]] **[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Jasikan|Jasikan]] **[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Keta–Akatsi|Keta–Akatsi]] **[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Koforidua|Koforidua]] **[[Roman Catholic Vicariate of Donkorkrom|Donkorkrom]] *[[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Cape Coast|Cape Coast]] **[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Sekondi–Takoradi|Sekondi–Takoradi]] **[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Wiawso|Wiawso]] *[[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Kumasi|Kumasi]] **[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Goaso|Goaso]] **[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Konongo–Mampong|Konongo–Mampong]] **[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Obuasi|Obuasi]] **[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Sunyani|Sunyani]] **[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Techiman|Techiman]] *[[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Tamale|Tamale]] **[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Damongo|Damongo]] **[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Navrongo–Bolgatanga|Navrongo–Bolgatanga]] **[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Wa|Wa]] **[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Yendi|Yendi]]
