The '''Former Liberation Movements of Southern Africa (FLMSA)''' is an association of six political parties which were involved in the nationalist movements of [[Southern Africa]]. It has its roots in the [[Frontline States]].<ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=7 March 2013 |title=President in SA for former liberation movements meeting |url=http://www.herald.co.zw/president-in-sa-for-former-liberation-movements-meeting/ |newspaper= [[The Herald (Zimbabwe)]] |location= |publisher= |accessdate=23 October 2013 }}</ref>

