{{refimprove|date=December 2015}}
The '''Hooper baronets''', of Tenterden in the County of Kent, was a title in the [[Baronetage of the United Kingdom]]. It was created on 11 July 1962 for Frederic Hooper, Managing Director of the [[Schweppes|Schweppes Group of Companies]] and adviser on Recruiting to the [[Minister of Defence (United Kingdom)|Minister of Defence]]. The title became extinct on the death of the second Baronet in 1987.

==Hooper baronets, of Tenterden (1962)==
*Sir Frederic Collins Hooper, 1st Baronet (1892–1963)
*Sir Anthony Robin Maurice Hooper, 2nd Baronet (1918–1987)

