{{Infobox political party |country = Andorra |name = Lauredian Union |native_name = Unió Laurediana |colorcode = green |logo = |leader = |foundation = |predecessor = |ideology = [[Conservatism]]<ref name="Nordsieck">{{Cite web|url=http://parties-and-elections.eu/andorra.html|title=Andorra|last=Nordsieck|first=Wolfram|date=2015|website=Parties and Elections in Europe|access-date=9 April 2018}}</ref><ref name="Lansford2013"/> |headquarters =[[Sant Julià de Lòria]] |colours = |international = |position = [[Centre-right]] |seats1_title = [[General Council (Andorra)|General Council]] |seats1 = {{Composition bar|0|28|hex=green}} |website = }} {{Politics of Andorra}}
The '''Lauredian Union''' ({{lang-ca|Unió Laurediana}}, UL) is a [[Conservatism|conservative]]<ref name="Nordsieck"/><ref name="Lansford2013">{{cite book|author=Tom Lansford|title=Political Handbook of the World 2013|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=lUF1AwAAQBAJ&pg=PA37|date=15 April 2013|publisher=SAGE Publications|isbn=978-1-4522-5825-6|page=37}}</ref> [[political party]] in [[Sant Julià de Lòria]], [[Andorra]].
==History== The party first contested national elections in 1997,<ref name=NS>[[Dieter Nohlen|Nohlen D]] & Stöver P (2010) ''Elections in Europe: A data handbook'', p162 {{ISBN|978-3-8329-5609-7}}</ref> when it was one of several local parties to form an alliance with the [[Liberal Party of Andorra|Liberal Union]] in the [[Andorran parliamentary election, 1997|parliamentary elections]] that year. The UL failed to win a seat,<ref name=NS/> but in the [[Andorran parliamentary election, 2001|2001 elections]] won two seats.<ref>Nohlen & Stöver, p165</ref> The party did not contest the [[Andorran parliamentary election, 2005|2005 elections]],<ref name=NS/>
For the [[Andorran parliamentary election, 2009|2009 elections]] the party was part of the [[Reformist Coalition]], which won 11 of the 28 seats.<ref>[http://www.ipu.org/parline-e/reports/arc/2005_09.htm Elections in 2009] IPU</ref> In the [[Andorran parliamentary election, 2011|2011 elections]] the party won two seats,<ref>[http://www.ipu.org/parline-e/reports/2005_E.htm Latest elections] IPU</ref> supporting [[Democrats for Andorra]].<ref name="Lansford2013"/>
