The '''Lithuanian Actuarial Society''' ({{lang-lt|Lietuvos aktuarijų draugija}}) is the association of [[actuary|actuaries]] in [[Lithuania]]. The Society was founded in 1996. In 2005, it became a full member of the [[Groupe Consultatif]]. As of 2011, the Society has 41 members. Current chairman of the Society is Rokas Gylys.<ref>[http://www.the-actuary.org.uk The Actuary], November 2006, p. 14</ref>

