{{Infobox Union |name= NKPU |country= [[Ukraine]] |affiliation= |members= 1.5 million (claimed) |full_name= National Confederation of the Trade-Union Organizations of Ukraine |native_name= |image= |founded= November 26, 2004 |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= |people= [[Petro Petrychenko]], secretary general |website= |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. -->
The '''National Confederation of the Trade-Union Organizations of Ukraine''' (NKPU) is a [[national trade union center]] in [[Ukraine]]. It was founded November 26, 2004 and claims a membership of 1.5 million.
The NKPU was formed as a breakaway union from the [[Federation of Trade Unions of Ukraine]].
