'''OMC Shipping pte. ltd.''', also known as '''OMCS''', is a [[Singapore]] based [[Ship-owner|ship owning]] company.<ref name="off">{{cite web |title=OMC Shipping - about us |url=http://www.omcs.com.sg/ |website=www.omcs.com.sg |publisher=OMC Shipping official website |accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref> It is the ship owning arm of [[Mitsui & Co.]], one of the largest [[Sogo shosha|trading companies ''(sogo sosha)'' of Japan]].<ref name="rpt">{{cite book |title=Annual shareholders report |date=1 September 2017 |publisher=Mitsui & Co. |location=Tokyo Japan |url=https://www.mitsui.com/jp/en/ir/library/report/__icsFiles/afieldfile/2017/09/06/en_ar2017_all_1.pdf |accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref>
==Fleet== OMC owns, operates and manages a fleet of 19 ships.<ref>{{cite web |title=Our fleet |url=http://www.omcs.com.sg/our-fleet/ |website=OMC Shipping official website |publisher=OMC Shipping |accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref> This includes [[bulk carrier]]s (handy size to cape size), [[oil tankers]] (product and crude oil), [[Pure car carrier|car carriers]] (PCTC of size 8000 CEU) and [[container ships]] (up to 9700 TEU in size).<ref>{{cite web |title=Company Financial information |url=https://www.mitsui.com/jp/en/ir/data/index.html |website=Official website - Mitsui & Co - financial |publisher=Mitsui & Co. |accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref> The company also charters these ships out on time charters and voyage charters.<ref>{{cite web |title=Our operations |url=http://www.omcs.com.sg/about-us/#operation |website=OMC Shipping - operations |publisher=OMCS |accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref> The company also owns and operates additional ships on short and [[Time Charter|long term charters]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Singapore brokers gather at Institute of Chartered Shipbrokers awards night |url=http://www.tradewindsnews.com/weekly/385460/singapore-brokers-gather-at-institute-of-chartered-shipbrokers-awards-night |accessdate=8 June 2018 |publisher=Tradewinds}}</ref>
