[[File:Politeama Rossetti Trieste.jpg|thumb|right|320px|Façade of Politeama Rossetti]]
'''Politeama Rossetti''' is an Italian theatre situated in the city of [[Trieste]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.connessomagazine.it/nek-e-il-suo-european-tour-2011-ad-aprile-al-politeama-rossetti-di-trieste|title=Nek e il suo European Tour 2011 ad aprile a al Politeama Rossetti di Trieste|date=2011-02-02|publisher=Connesso Magazine|language=Italian|accessdate=25 July 2011}}</ref> With over 60 shows scheduled each season, running from October to June, its stage shows include plays, musicals, ballet, dance and rock concerts.

It is the home of Teatro Stabile del Friuli Venezia Giulia, one of Italy's major public theatres. The artistic director is Antonio Calenda.

The theatre was built in 1878 and designed by Nicolò Bruno. It was heavily restored in 1928, 1969 and 1999. While the original capacity was over 5,000, it can now sit 1,531.

In the recent years the theatre has specialised in the presentation of major West End and Broadway musicals, including the original productions of ''[[Cats (musical)|Cats]]'' in 2008, ''[[Mamma Mia!]]'', ''[[The Rocky Horror Show]]''<ref>{{cite news|title=Bello Rocky Horror come appena scritto|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2009/04/06/bello-rocky-horror-come-appena-scritto.html|accessdate=25 July 2011|newspaper=La Repubblica|date=2009-04-06}}</ref>  and ''[[Chicago (musical)|Chicago]]'' in 2009. In 2010 the theatre staged ''[[We Will Rock You]]'', featuring the music of Queen, the acclaimed 50th anniversary production of ''[[West Side Story]]'' and Andrew Lloyd Webber’s ''[[Evita (musical)|Evita]]''. In 2011 the theatre hosted the Italian premieres of the musicals ''[[Chess (musical)|Chess]]'' and ''[[Spamalot]]''.

