The '''Diocese of Acerno''' was a [[Roman Catholic]] [[diocese]] based in [[Acerno]] near [[Naples]] in southern [[Italy]], with the bishop's seat in [[Acerno Cathedral]]. Created in the 11th century, it was suppressed in 1818, when it was merged with the [[Diocese of Salerno]] to create the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Salerno-Campagna-Acerno|Archdiocese of Salerno-Acerno]].<ref name=CathHierAcerno>{{Cite web|last=Cheney |first=David M.|authorlink=|title=Diocese of Acerno |publisher=''[[Catholic-Hierarchy.org]]''|date=|url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/da218.html|accessdate=June 16, 2018}}[[Wikipedia:Verifiability#Self-published sources|{{sup|''self-published''}}]]</ref><ref name=GCathAcerno>{{Cite web|last=Chow |first=Gabriel|authorlink=|title=Diocese of Acerno |publisher=''[[GCatholic.org]]''|date=|url=http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/former/acer2.htm |accessdate=June 16, 2018}}[[Wikipedia:Verifiability#Self-published sources|{{sup|''self-published''}}]]</ref>
