[[File:Indestructible Sofia. Picture by Yuri Khimich. Ukrainian stamp, 2005.jpg|thumb|''The Indestructible [[Saint Sophia's Cathedral, Kiev|Sofia]] (of Kiev)''. Painting by Yuriy Khimich, 1965. Ukrainian stamp, 2005, 80 kop.]] '''Yuriy Ivanovich Khimich''' ({{lang-uk|Химич Юрій Іванович}}: April 12, 1928 in [[Kamianets-Podilskyi]]&ndash;2003) was a [[Ukrainians|Ukrainian]] painter.<ref>http://neboartgallery.com.ua/eng/contents/authview?id=64</ref> He worked primarily in water colours and oil. He was an honoured artist of the Ukraine.
He painted traditional and historic buildings, such as churches and monasteries, but also cityscapes and landscapes. His works of art are located in various museums today. He was honoured with a Ukrainian stamp in 2005 with his depiction of [[Saint Sophia's Cathedral, Kiev]].
